{
  "doc_id": "33012",
  "text": "We have proved in Coq the soundness of Separation Logic for Cminor. Each rule is proved as a lemma; in addition there is a main theorem that if you prove all your function bodies satisfy their pre/postconditions, then the program \"call main()\" is safe. We have informally tested the adequacy of our result by doing tactical proofs of small programs [CITATION_1] . ",
